videos.description: After a slow start, Cal finally gets on the board first when Davis Webb tosses a perfect fade pass to Demetris Robertson for the 10-yard touchdown to go up 7-0 on Oregon.
videos.headline: Cal strikes first with the perfect fade pass

videos.description: Davis Webb shows off his touch with the loft pass to Raymond Hudson for the five-yard touchdown to put Cal up 14-0 over Oregon just before the end of the first quarter.
videos.headline: Webb strikes again for 2nd TD in the first quarter

videos.description: Cal's hot start continues as Davis Webb hits Vic Wharton III from 13 yards out to make it 21-0 Cal early in the second quarter.
videos.headline: Webb tosses third TD to third different receiver

videos.description: After falling into a 21 point hole, the Oregon offense wakes up when Justin Herbert hits Pharaoh Brown for the 27-yard touchdown to cut Cal's lead to 21-7.
videos.headline: Oregon finally strikes back with 27-yard TD to Brown

videos.description: Oregon is starting to rev up in come back mode when Tony Brooks-James, after busting off a long run to get to the goal line, finishes the job punching it into the end zone from a yard out to cut Oregon's deficit to 10.
videos.headline: Brooks-James punches it in to get Oregon closer

videos.description: With the first half clock ticking down, Cal runs a misdirection play that leaves Tre Watson wide open to find Davis Webb for his fourth passing touchdown of the game, boosting Cal's lead to 31-14.
videos.headline: Webb makes it four passing TDs in the first half for Cal

videos.description: From the one-yard line, Oregon runs the play-action pass to perfection when Justin Herbert finds Evan Baylis in the back of the end zone to cut the Ducks' deficit to 34-21.
videos.headline: Oregon runs play-action to perfection to cut into Cal's lead

videos.description: Oregon cuts it down to a one-score game when Justin Herbert keeps on the option and finds Johnny Mundt wide open over the middle for the touchdown to get the Ducks back to 34-28.
videos.headline: Oregon continues comeback bid with another touchdown

videos.description: Tre Watson run for a loss of 1 yard to the Cal 44
videos.headline: Oregon stuffs Cal on 4th down

videos.description: Trailing by 21 points to start the game, Oregon claws all the way back to take the lead for the first time in the game when Justin Herbert hits Charles Nelson for a six-yard touchdown for a Ducks' 35-34 lead.
videos.headline: Herbert's laser toss puts Oregon ahead for the first time

videos.description: With the blitz coming, Davis Webb rolls out and makes the throw to a diving Tre Watson for a 14-yard touchdown to give Cal back the lead at 42-35.
videos.headline: Awesome diving catch makes it 5 TD passes for Webb

videos.description: (D. Webb pass  to J. Hinnant for Two-Point Conversion)
videos.headline: D. Webb pass to J. Hinnant for Two-Point Conversion

videos.description: Oregon punches back to tie the game when Charles Nelson makes the catch in open space and goes to the house for a 42-yard touchdown pushing the score to 42-42.
videos.headline: Oregon strikes quick with 42-yard TD to send game to OT
Cal misses winning field goal at end of regulation

videos.headline: J. Herbert pass to J. Brown for 20 yds for a TD

Anderson field goal gives Cal lead in double overtime

videos.description: In the latest wild edition of "Pac-12 After Dark," Cal's Jordan Kunaszyk picks off Justin Herbert, the only turnover of the game, to clinch a frantic 52-49 win over Oregon in double-overtime.
videos.headline: Interception in 2OT wins wild game for Cal
